<http://www.spektrix.com/ticketseller/event/14201ARTVMVMMBMSJNNDBHCBBRVSCTRNG> a schema:Event;
  schema:name "I Am Woman, Hear Me Laff!";
  schema:description """
	<span class=\"BoldText\">$45.00 Per Person</span><span><br/></span>Including fees & charges<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">UPDATED! Full Lineup Announced!</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Fans of VDPAC’s annual celebration of International Women’s Day, <span class=\"BoldText\">I Am Woman, Hear Me Laff!</span> will recognize this year’s featured headliner, <span class=\"BoldText\">Julie Kim</span> as the host and emcee in 2024 for the headlining Canadian comedic icon, <span class=\"BoldText\">Elvira Kurt</span>.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Julie Kim</span> is one of Canada’s premiere stand-up comedians. Julie toured across Canada last Fall, performing with <span class=\"BoldText\">Rick Mercer</span> on the Stand-Up for Canada Tour. She was also a gala performer at the 2022 Just for Laughs Festival in Montreal and headlined four sold-out solo shows at Just for Laughs Toronto in 2023.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Over the past decade, Julie has performed at all the major Canadian comedy festivals and has toured Australia and the United Kingdom. Julie has also been regularly featured on CBC Radio’s The Debaters with Steve Patterson.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Special Guest</span>: Remember “Kevin”? Then you’ll remember <span class=\"BoldText\">Yumi Nagashima</span>! In less than 3 years, this Vancouver based, Japanese-Canadian comic and actress has made a huge splash on the North American comedy scene with her sassy stage presence, unique world view and deceptively demure delivery. A mainstay in the Vancouver comedy world, she is a listener favourite on CBC Radio’s The Debaters; on TV from the Winnipeg Comedy Festival; and featured as part of Just For Laughs Northwest. Visit the “Yumiverse” at: <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.instagram.com/yumicomedy/?hl=en\">Yumi Nagashima (@yumicomedy) • Instagram photos and videos</a><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Special Guest MC</span>: VDPAC welcomes <span class=\"BoldText\">Michaela Chung</span>, a Vancouver based comedian and author, known for her sharp wit and relatable stories. She regularly performs in comedy clubs across Canada and has been featured in ABC, CBC, Forbes and Just For Laughs. You can hear her comedy on SiriusXM and her album Daddy Issues, represented by 604 Studios. Visit: <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.instagram.com/michaelachung1/?hl=en\">Michaela Chung (@michaelachung1) • Instagram photos and videos</a><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">JOIN US!</span> For VDPAC’s 21st Annual Celebration of International Women’s Day, <span class=\"BoldText\">I Am Woman, Hear Me Laff!</span> Grab your besties and get ready for a sizzling night of female empowerment guaranteed to deliver side-splitting, tear-inducing laughter!<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\"><span class=\"ItalicText\">CAUTION: It gets SPICY! May contain 19+ strong language & mature content.</span></span>
""";
